FBIS3-12532 "drnes041_l_94014" FBIS-NES-94-041 Document Type:Daily Report 2 Mar 1994 ISRAEL Police Chief Says Territories To Remain Closed TA0203123094 Tel Aviv IDF Radio in Hebrew 1100 GMT 2 Mar 94 TA0203123094 Tel Aviv IDF Radio Language: Hebrew Article Type:BFN [Text] Police Commissioner Rafi Peled says the increased police deployment introduced following the Hebron massacre will continue for the time being. Touring the south, the commissioner said the closure on the Gaza Strip and the territories in general will continue until the tension, which arose in the wake of the massacre, dissipates. [Begin Peled recording] Right now the thing to do is to calm the situation. People in charge should have an opportunity to organize and calm flaring tempers. I think, therefore, that the closure is the right answer at this time. The beefed-up police deployment will also continue as long as necessary. [end recording]
